<h3 dir="auto" class="">Key Changes:</h3>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><strong>Argument Parsing with <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">argparse</span></strong>:
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">Added <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">argparse</span> to handle an optional file argument (<span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">file</span>).</li>
<li class="break-words">Usage examples are updated in the docstring: run with a specific file (<span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">python extract_mhtml_text.py file.mhtml</span>) or without arguments (<span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">python extract_mhtml_text.py</span>).</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong>Single File Processing</strong>:
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">The <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">process_file</span> function handles processing a single MHTML file, including error checks for file existence and type.</li>
<li class="break-words">If a file is passed as an argument, only that file is processed, and the script exits.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong>Interactive Prompt</strong>:
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">If no argument is provided, the script finds all <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">.mhtml</span> files in the current directory using <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">glob</span>.</li>
<li class="break-words">It lists the files and prompts the user with "Do you want to process all of these files? (yes/no)".</li>
<li class="break-words">If the user responds with "yes" or "y" (case-insensitive), all files are processed; otherwise, the script exits without processing.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong>Error Handling</strong>:
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">Added checks to ensure the specified file exists and is an <span class="text-sm px-1 rounded-sm !font-mono bg-sunset/10 text-rust dark:bg-dawn/10 dark:text-dawn">.mhtml</span> file when a single file is provided.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
